wikipedia_page.main: Bryan Ricco Cooper (17 June 1884 – 5 July 1930) was an Irish politician, writer and landowner from Markree Castle, County Sligo. He was prominent in Dáil Éireann in the early years of the Irish Free State, having previously served as MP to Westminster for South County Dublin (1910), a seat he subsequently represented in the Dáil from 1923 to 1930.
